Concrete Strength Prediction¶

Objective¶

To predict the concrete strength using the data available in file concrete_data.xls. Apply feature engineering and model tuning to obtain 80% to 95% of R2score.

Resources Available¶

The data for this project is available in file https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/concrete/compressive/. The same has been shared along with the course content.

Attribute Information:¶

Given are the variable name, variable type, the measurement unit and a brief description. The concrete compressive strength is the regression problem. The order of this listing corresponds to the order of numerals along the rows of the database.

Name -- Data Type -- Measurement -- Description
Cement (cement) -- quantitative -- kg in a m3 mixture -- Input Variable
Blast Furnace Slag (slag) -- quantitative -- kg in a m3 mixture -- Input Variable
Fly Ash (ash) -- quantitative -- kg in a m3 mixture -- Input Variable
Water (water) -- quantitative -- kg in a m3 mixture -- Input Variable
Superplasticizer (superplastic) -- quantitative -- kg in a m3 mixture -- Input Variable
Coarse Aggregate (coarseagg) -- quantitative -- kg in a m3 mixture -- Input Variable
Fine Aggregate (fineagg) -- quantitative -- kg in a m3 mixture -- Input Variable
Age(age) -- quantitative -- Day (1~365) -- Input Variable
Concrete compressive strength(strength) -- quantitative -- MPa -- Output Variable

def df_col_analysis(df, fieldName, targetfield):
    maxVal= df[fieldName].max()
    minVal=df[fieldName].min()
    Q1=df[fieldName].quantile(q=0.25)
    Q3=df[fieldName].quantile(q=0.75)
    L_outliers=Q1-1.5*(Q3-Q1)
    U_outliers=Q3+1.5*(Q3-Q1)
    print(fieldName + ': Range : ', minVal, '-', maxVal)
    print(fieldName + ': Mean : ', df[fieldName].mean())
    print(fieldName + ': Median : ', df[fieldName].median())
    print(fieldName + ': Std Dev : ', df[fieldName].std())
    print(fieldName + ': Lower outliers : ', L_outliers)
    print(fieldName + ': upper outliers : ', U_outliers)
    print(fieldName + ': Number of outliers in  upper : ', df[df[fieldName]>U_outliers][fieldName].count())
    print(fieldName + ': Number of outliers in  lower : ', df[df[fieldName]<L_outliers][fieldName].count())
    print(fieldName + ': % of Outlier in  upper: ',round(df[df[fieldName]>U_outliers][fieldName].count()*100/len(df)), '%')
    print(fieldName + ': % of Outlier in  lower: ',round(df[df[fieldName]<L_outliers][fieldName].count()*100/len(df)), '%')
    
    fig, (ax1,ax2,ax3)=plt.subplots(1,3,figsize=(13,5))

    #boxplot
    sns.boxplot(x=fieldName,data=df,orient='v',ax=ax1)
    ax1.set_ylabel(fieldName, fontsize=15)
    ax1.set_title('Distribution of '+ fieldName, fontsize=15)
    ax1.tick_params(labelsize=15)

    #distplot
    sns.distplot(df[fieldName],ax=ax2)
    ax2.set_xlabel(fieldName, fontsize=15)
    ax2.set_ylabel(targetfield, fontsize=15)
    plt.axvline(df[fieldName].mean(),linestyle="dashed",label="mean",color="k")
    plt.legend(loc="best")
    plt.xlabel("")
    ax2.set_title( fieldName + ' vs '+ targetfield, fontsize=15)
    ax2.tick_params(labelsize=15)

    #histogram
    ax3.hist(df[fieldName])
    ax3.set_xlabel(fieldName, fontsize=15)
    ax3.set_ylabel(targetfield, fontsize=15)
    ax3.set_title(fieldName + ' vs ' + targetfield, fontsize=15)
    ax3.tick_params(labelsize=15)

    plt.subplots_adjust(wspace=0.5)
    plt.tight_layout()

results_df = pd.DataFrame()

def execute_model(results_df, testName, dt_model, dtrainX, dtrainy, dtestX, dtesty, of_type, cv=True):
    print (dt_model)
    print("Columns:",dtrainX.columns) 
    dt_model=dt_model.fit(dtrainX, dtrainy)
    y_pred = dt_model.predict(dtestX)
    actual=dtesty
    predicted=y_pred
    
    tr_acc=dt_model.score(dtrainX,dtrainy)
    tst_acc=dt_model.score(dtestX, dtesty)
    acc_DT=metrics.r2_score(dtesty, y_pred)
    mse=metrics.mean_squared_error(dtesty, y_pred)
    rmse=np.sqrt(mse)
    print()   
    print("Training accuracy",tr_acc)  
    print()
    print("Testing accuracy",tst_acc)
    print()
    print('MEAN SQUARED ERROR: ',mse) 
    print ("ROOT MEAN SQUARED ERROR :", np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(dtesty,predicted)) )
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
    
    #printing the feature importance
    if of_type == "feat":
        print('Feature importances: \n',pd.DataFrame(dt_model.feature_importances_,columns=['Imp'],index=X_train.columns).sort_values(by=['Imp'], ascending=False))
        coef = pd.DataFrame(dt_model.feature_importances_)
        coef["feat"] = dtrainX.columns
        ax2 = sns.barplot(coef["feat"],coef[0],palette="jet_r",
                          linewidth=2,edgecolor="k"*coef["feat"].nunique())
        ax2.set_facecolor("lightgrey")
        ax2.axhline(0,color="k",linewidth=2)
        plt.ylabel("coefficients")
        plt.xlabel("features")
        plt.title('FEATURE IMPORTANCES')
    elif of_type == "coef":
        print('Coefficient importances: \n',pd.DataFrame(dt_model.coef_, X.columns, columns=['Coefficient']).sort_values(by=['Coefficient'], ascending=False))
        coef = pd.DataFrame(dt_model.coef_.ravel())
        coef["feat"] = dtrainX.columns
        ax1 = sns.barplot(coef["feat"],coef[0],palette="jet_r",
                          linewidth=2,edgecolor="k"*coef["feat"].nunique())
        ax1.set_facecolor("lightgrey")
        ax1.axhline(0,color="k",linewidth=2)
        plt.ylabel("coefficients")
        plt.xlabel("features")
        plt.title('FEATURE IMPORTANCES')
    elif of_type == "hyper":
        best_hyperparams = dt_model.best_params_ 
        print('Best hyerparameters:\n', best_hyperparams)

    cv_r2_mean=float("nan")
    stdDev=float("nan")
    if (cv) :
        num_folds = 10
        seed = 77
        kfold = KFold(n_splits=num_folds, random_state=seed)
        cross_val_rl = cross_val_score(dt_model,X, y, cv=kfold, scoring='r2')
        cv_r2_mean=np.mean(abs(cross_val_rl))
        stdDev=cross_val_rl.std()
        print ("CROSS VALIDATION SCORE")
        print ("************************")
        print('R2 mean: ',cv_r2_mean)
        print('Standard Deviation: ',stdDev)
        cross_val = cross_val_rl.ravel()  
        print ("cv-mean :",cross_val.mean())
        print ("cv-std  :",cross_val.std())
        print ("cv-max  :",cross_val.max())
        print ("cv-min  :",cross_val.min())
    
    
    resultMap= {'1_TestName' : testName, '1_cols_count': dtrainX.columns.size, '2_TrainingAccuracy' : tr_acc,
            '3_TestingAccuracy' : tst_acc, '3_r2_Acc':acc_DT,'4_MSE':mse, '4_RMSE':rmse,'5_KFold_R2_Mean' : cv_r2_mean,
            '5_KFold_Std_Dev' : stdDev}
    results_df=results_df.append(resultMap,ignore_index=True)
    
    return results_df;
